===============================================================================

ActiveIntelligence has been installed!

Next steps:

1. Run migrations:
   rails db:migrate

2. Configure your Anthropic API key:

   Option A - Environment variable (recommended):
   export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-ant-..."

   Option B - Rails credentials:
   rails credentials:edit
   # Add: anthropic: { api_key: "sk-ant-..." }

3. Create your first agent:

   # app/agents/my_agent.rb
   class MyAgent < ActiveIntelligence::Agent
     model :claude
     memory :active_record
     identity "You are a helpful assistant"

     # Register your tools
     # tool MyCustomTool
   end

4. Use in your controller:

   class ConversationsController < ApplicationController
     include ActiveIntelligence::ConversationManageable

     def create
       @conversation = create_conversation(
         agent_class: 'MyAgent',
         objective: params[:objective]
       )
       render json: { id: @conversation.id }
     end

     def send_message
       conversation = find_conversation(params[:id])
       response = send_agent_message(params[:message], conversation: conversation)
       render json: { response: response }
     end
   end

5. For streaming support:

   class ConversationsController < ApplicationController
     include ActionController::Live
     include ActiveIntelligence::ConversationManageable

     def send_message_streaming
       conversation = find_conversation(params[:id])

       send_agent_message_streaming(params[:message], conversation: conversation)
     end
   end

Files created:
  - config/initializers/active_intelligence.rb
  - db/migrate/..._create_active_intelligence_conversations.rb
  - db/migrate/..._create_active_intelligence_messages.rb
  - app/models/active_intelligence/conversation.rb
  - app/models/active_intelligence/message.rb
  - app/controllers/concerns/active_intelligence/conversation_manageable.rb

